<br>
Any way, I'm holding off updating my list again until PoP comes out and we have semi-finalized numbers.<br>
-------------------------------------<br>
OK, time to revamp my list for PoP.  My proposed changes for pre-PoP spells still stand.  In addition, I'm adding PoP nukes to the comparison and I'll be making comments on how they might be tweaked.<br>
<br>
My end goal is to have Wizard come out on top in every catagory:  DPS, ratio, and variety.  Magi and Druids should be equal in variety.  For ratio, Druids should be superior to Magi, because Mage pets far outweigh Druid DoTs in terms of effeciency.  On the flip side, Magi should beat Druids in short term DPS because Magi conjure pure elements, whilst Druids draw from nature (I think raw elements have more sheer power than indirectly calling on nature, but this is merely a personal opinion).<br>
<br>
Ahh, what the heck.  Adding other classes too.<br>
<br>
Ooops, first a few notes:<br>
<br>
1).  DPS is used as theoretical DPS chain casting that particular spell.<br>
2).  Rains were left out of the comparison due to being on a different resist table, and their situational usage.<br>
3.)  DPS calculates <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>          may</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be off just slightly, due to a varience in recovery time from spell to spell.  I'm using a flat 2.25 seconds of recovery time for each spell, when in reality I believe some have 2.5.  I'm fairly sure none are lower than 2.25, however.  Also, it is possible to &quot;cheat&quot; the recovery time, by using a right-click item with an instant effect, immediately after landing a spell, such as JBoots or SoTF (not to be confused with SotF).<br>
