<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>          Comments based on what is currently known about possible PoP spells:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>         1.)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Wizards remain the undisputed kings of DPS.  Put several lvl 65 Wizards in a group with some class that has good group heals/regens and you can put out some absolutely staggering damage (nearly double the DPS of EER).  I strongly suspect that SoS will be the GSS of PoP.  Good luck over obtaining that spell.  If we ignore SoS for a moment, Wizards actually get very modest improvements over SoL.  Iceflame of E'ci has the potential to be a very nice spell, ratio-wise.  ISoS/A<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> oI combine with IE will be effecient to the extreme.  Some of the Wizard Draughts are very puzzling with their ratios, however.  Particularly baffling is why their PoP Cold Draught will be lesse effective than their Kunark Cold Draught, when using EI.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>         2.)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Countrary to popular belief, Magi are being treated <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>         extremely</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> well with PoP nukes.  Magi get nukes which actually come close to Wizard nukes in ratio, pass Druid ratios--both Firebolt of Tallon and Black Steel--and yet still manage to stay ahead of Druids DPS-wise.  This is a complete coup by Mage nukes and instead of whining about nukes, if I still played a Mage I would shut up and try to stop all discussion so VI  won't realize how much they really boosted Mage nuking.  This could turn out to be the best expansion ever for Magi, damage-wise (and isn't that what you want?)<br>
