I haven't had a chance to analyze all the spells for this expansion in depth, but after a moderately careful look over the spell list Wizard Draughts seem very lacking.  For non-EER/GSS Wizards (which is the catagory most lvl 60 Wizards currently fall into) they must wait all the way until 64 to get a really shining nuke.  This is assuming that AT will be buyable/easily attainable (which is the usual pattern for nukes prior to the last lvl of an expansion).  Tenatively, PoP Draughts should have their damage increased accross the board--at least enough for the PoP Cold Draught to still be better than the Kunark Cold Draught when using EI (EI only effects spells upto lvl 60).<br>
