bs that cannot be rooted or snared by PCs, but can be rooted by an earth elemental.  And the elemental itself greatly effects the movement of the mob: that's how we solo.<br>
<br>
I have had the joy of using snare and root with alts, but still, give me <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> the inability to help in groups<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Learn to use what you have.  We do <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>just</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> fine in groups.  Steady damage, through pets and nukes, limited crowd control through pets, burn down when needed, summons when needed, and starting 49th level, the ability to recover fairly quickly after burning down your mana bar.  Later on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Call of the Hero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to bring in raiders or groupmates across obstacles, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rods of Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to generate and move mana around.  Damage shields to bring the fight to an end sooner, dispells to remove buffs.<br>
<br>
Master the abilities that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Karana</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, in his infinite wisdom, has rained down upon you like pennies from heaven, and you will discover that you are quite awesome in groups.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So when talking about nukes please dont drag the pets in?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Absurd.  How can magicians be evaluated reasonably without bringing pets into the picture.  That would be like warriors complaining about the lack of gate without taking into account their ability to tank.  You can complain about anything in isolation.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Mages have been raked over hot coals since the begining of the game for their pets<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yes, this <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>was</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> true, we have suffered mightily, but starting with the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Great Patch</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and neutral pets, the sun has been rising for mages.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ALL of these problems can be solved with a GOOD focus item system....Like one that scales dependent on loot tables for meelee...<br>
<br>
Rogues did not just get patched and then became the master of dmg...No, new weapons began droping for them that uped their dps....Like...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I will agree that focus items are not as well thought out as they might have been, but the fact that melees are improved more by items than casters are arises naturally from the fact that melees are dependent on gear while casters are not.  True, the balance has been biased in favor of melee, and might still be, but casters have far and away the best magic item in the game: their spell book.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Why oh WHY verant do u make us power reliant on lvl rather then Items...*sigh* Focus items to casters should be like dmg/delay to meelees.....And FT should be like haste...Its so simple :P<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It's not that simple.<br>
<br>
We casters derive the vast majority of our power from within ourselves, in particular our spell book.  Melees require weapons and armor to act effectively.  A naked caster is more powerful than a naked melee.  The balance is that gear improves melees more than it improves casters.<br>
<br>
If casters were as improved by gear as melees are, then we would simply dominate them.  A good weapon can easily double the sustained damage output of a melee compared to a more common weapon.  If I could hold a wand that doubled <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>my</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> damage output, then people would abandon rogues and monks in droves, and all we would need are mages and druids, and a smattering of other classes.<br>
